article.description: Bakari Evelyn hit a jumper with 11 seconds left in regulation to force overtime and Valparaiso limited SIU-Edwardsville to just two points in the extra period to post a 75-70 victory Wednesday night.
article.headline: Valparaiso shuts down SIU-Edwardsville in overtime, 75-70
article.linkText: Valparaiso shuts down SIU-Edwardsville in overtime, 75-70
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Bakari Evelyn hit a jumper with 11 seconds left in regulation to force overtime and Valparaiso limited SIU-Edwardsville to just two points in the extra period to post a 75-70 victory Wednesday night. The Crusaders bounced back from a 69-63 loss to Wake Forest to win their third game in five starts. Evelyn tied the game at 65-65 with 1:56 left on a layup, but Tyresse Williford put the Cougars up by two with :20 remaining. Coming out of a Valpo time out, Evelyn tied the game again at 68-68 with a jumper to force the extra period and got to the basket in the first minute of overtime to take the lead. Brandon Jackson hit a jumper with 1:35 left to get SIUE even at 70-70, but it could not score again. Evelyn finished with 16 points to lead Valpo and lead five players in double-figure scoring. Williford finished with 24 points and Cameron Williams added 22 for SIUE.
